This paper is primarily focused on developing an AI algorithm to play a game against human players, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of cognitive hierarchy theory and Bayesian learning techniques also suggests that this paper could be categorized under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves testing the AI algorithm against human players. Finally, the use of a game as a testing ground for AI decision-making could also fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
